I added a second version of the example that does not require the `matches` method or searching the DOM for each individual checkbox by class or ID.  If you can structure the HTML and data object that holds the users&#39; preferences in a similar manner, you can traverse the DOM and make use of the HTML data attribute to simplify the code further.

